question: How do I reset my portal password?
answer: Use the Forgot Password link on the sign-in page, then confirm via the email OTP.

question: What is the SLA for premium customers?
answer: Premium customers receive a 2-hour first-response SLA and 24-hour resolution commitment.

question: Can I upgrade my plan mid-cycle?
answer: Yes, upgrades take effect immediately and the difference is prorated on your next invoice.

question: How do I track my shipment?
answer: Go to Orders > Track Shipment in the dashboard; the tracking ID syncs every 15 minutes.

question: Where do I download invoices?
answer: Navigate to Billing > Invoices. You can export PDF or CSV versions for each month.

question: How do I change the primary email on my account?
answer: Visit Settings > Profile, edit the email field, and confirm the verification email we send within 15 minutes.

question: Why was my payment declined?
answer: Payments can fail due to expired cards or bank restrictions. Update your card under Billing > Payment Methods or contact your bank.

question: Can I add multiple team members?
answer: Yes, go to Settings > Team, click Add Member, and assign roles such as Admin or Viewer.

question: How do I export all support tickets?
answer: Open Support > Tickets and use the Export button in the top-right to download a CSV of filtered results.

question: Does the system support SSO?
answer: Yes, SAML 2.0 and OAuth SSO are available on Enterprise plans. Contact support to enable it.

question: How can I pause my subscription?
answer: Navigate to Billing > Plans, choose Pause Plan, and select a resume date within 90 days.

question: What browsers are supported?
answer: We support the latest two versions of Chrome, Edge, Firefox, and Safari. Older versions may display warnings.

question: How do I enable two-factor authentication?
answer: Under Settings > Security toggle 2FA, scan the QR code with your authenticator app, and enter the generated code.

question: Can I connect my Slack workspace?
answer: Yes, Settings > Integrations > Slack lets you authorize the bot and choose which channel receives alerts.

question: Where can I see system status updates?
answer: Visit status.example.com for real-time uptime, planned maintenance, and incident history.

question: How do I delete my account?
answer: Submit a deletion request under Settings > Privacy. We process it within 7 days and send a confirmation email.

question: What file types can I upload?
answer: We accept PDF, DOCX, XLSX, PNG, and JPG up to 25 MB each.

question: How do I revert to a previous version of a document?
answer: Open the document, click History, and select Restore next to the desired timestamp.

question: Is there an API rate limit?
answer: Yes, the default limit is 120 requests per minute per API key. Contact support for higher tiers.

question: Can I receive invoices via email automatically?
answer: Enable email delivery in Billing > Preferences to receive PDF invoices at the end of each cycle.

question: How do I submit feature requests?
answer: Use the in-app Feedback button or email product@example.com with a detailed description and impact.

question: Why can't I log in with Google?
answer: Ensure your workspace admin enabled Google Sign-In under Settings > Authentication and that your Google email matches.

question: How do I change my notification preferences?
answer: Go to Settings > Notifications and toggle the channels (email, SMS, in-app) for each alert type.

question: Can I set up automatic reminders for open tasks?
answer: Yes, in Tasks > Automations you can schedule reminders by due date or priority level.

question: What regions are data stored in?
answer: Data is stored in AWS regions US-East-1 and EU-West-1 with nightly backups retained for 30 days.

question: How do I whitelist your email domain?
answer: Share support@example.com and mail.example.com with your IT team to whitelist on your email gateway.

question: Can I integrate with Salesforce?
answer: Yes, enable the Salesforce connector under Integrations and map the fields you want synced.

question: Where can I view usage analytics?
answer: Navigate to Analytics > Usage to view daily active users, feature adoption, and export charts.

question: How do I reset MFA for a user?
answer: Admins can go to Settings > Team, select the user, and click Reset MFA to force a new enrollment.

question: Can I customize the customer portal branding?
answer: Yes, under Settings > Branding upload your logo, select colors, and preview changes before publishing.

question: How do refunds work?
answer: Refunds can be issued within 30 days. Submit the request via Billing > Transactions and include the invoice ID.

question: What phone number should customers call?
answer: Our toll-free support line is +1-800-555-0199, available 9am–9pm IST Monday through Saturday.

question: Why is my integration showing stale data?
answer: Most integrations sync every 15 minutes. Check Integrations > Sync Logs to see the last successful sync.

question: Can I schedule reports to email automatically?
answer: Yes, in Analytics > Reports choose Schedule, set the frequency, and enter recipient emails.

question: Do you support multi-language content?
answer: The app supports English, Spanish, and Hindi UI strings. Knowledge base articles can be localized manually.

question: How do I manage API keys?
answer: Navigate to Developers > API Keys to create, revoke, or rotate keys. Each key inherits workspace permissions.

question: What happens if I exceed storage limits?
answer: You’ll receive alerts at 80% usage and overages will be billed per GB at month-end unless you upgrade storage.

question: How do I invite external collaborators?
answer: Use Share > Invite External and provide their email. They receive a guest link with restricted permissions.

question: Why did I receive a suspicious login alert?
answer: We detected a login from an unrecognized device or location. Review the session under Settings > Security and revoke if unsure.

question: How can I archive completed projects?
answer: Open Projects, select the project, click Archive. You can restore it anytime from the Archived tab.

question: Can I bulk import contacts?
answer: Yes, go to Contacts > Import, download the CSV template, fill it out, and upload. We validate and summarize errors.

question: How do I enable dark mode?
answer: Under Settings > Appearance toggle Dark Mode. The preference syncs across devices linked to your profile.

question: Is there a mobile app?
answer: Yes, iOS and Android apps are available. Download from the App Store or Google Play and log in with your credentials.

question: How do I escalate a support ticket?
answer: Inside a ticket, click Escalate and choose severity. A manager is notified within 10 minutes.

question: Can I automate webhooks on ticket updates?
answer: Yes, create webhook rules under Developers > Webhooks and select the events (created, updated, closed).

question: What is the backup policy?
answer: Full backups run nightly with point-in-time recovery for 7 days. Disaster recovery RTO is 2 hours.

question: Why are email notifications delayed?
answer: High-volume campaigns queue up. Check Email > Deliverability for queue status and throttle settings.

question: How do I view audit logs?
answer: Enterprise plans have Logs under Settings > Compliance where you can search by user, action, or date range.

question: Can I customize ticket fields?
answer: Yes, go to Support > Custom Fields and add dropdowns, text, or checkbox fields. They appear in forms immediately.

question: How do I change the default currency?
answer: Under Billing > Preferences select the new currency. Future invoices use the new currency; past invoices remain unchanged.

question: What training resources are available?
answer: Visit help.example.com/academy for on-demand videos, webinars, and certification tracks.

question: How do I submit a GDPR request?
answer: Use Settings > Privacy > Data Subject Request to submit access or deletion requests for EU customers.

question: Can I see which IPs accessed my account?
answer: Yes, Settings > Security > Login Activity lists IPs, browsers, and timestamps for the last 90 days.

question: What happens if Uplink Studios exceeds the 99% storage threshold?
answer: We notify the Uplink Studios admins when usage crosses 99%. They can archive data or purchase add-on storage from Billing > Storage.

question: How do I enable email notifications for Vanguard Realty?
answer: In Settings > Notifications turn on email for each queue serving Vanguard Realty. Remind agents to verify their email identity.

question: How can I audit renewal activity for Wildflower Spa?
answer: Visit Compliance > Audit Logs, filter by renewal, and export the CSV to review every step completed for Wildflower Spa.

question: How do I update the admin console branding for Yukon Timber?
answer: Navigate to Settings > Branding, upload the Yukon Timber logo, adjust colors, and publish to instantly refresh the admin console.

question: Can Zodiac Lighting allow guest access during escalation?
answer: Yes, enable Guest Links under Settings > Access, specify the escalation workspace, and set an expiry for Zodiac Lighting.

question: How do I clone automation rules for Acme Retail?
answer: Go to Automations, open the rule, click Clone, select the Acme Retail workspace, and review the triggers before saving.

question: What logs show Push delivery for Beta Logistics?
answer: Use Messaging > Delivery Logs to filter by Push and the Beta Logistics account to validate each event.

question: How do I reset API credentials for Cobalt Finance?
answer: Administrators can regenerate keys under Developers > API Keys. Inform Cobalt Finance to rotate credentials in downstream systems.

question: How do I route SMS conversations to Tier 2 for Delta Foods?
answer: Create a routing rule in Support > Queues targeting SMS and assign Tier 2 as the destination for Delta Foods.

question: Can I bulk import assets for Echo Airlines?
answer: Yes, go to Assets > Import, download the template, fill it with the Echo Airlines data, and upload. Validation errors will list row numbers.

question: How do I enforce IP restrictions for Falcon Manufacturing?
answer: Turn on IP Allow Lists under Security, enter the Falcon Manufacturing corporate ranges, and require re-login so the policy applies.

question: How do I create custom fields for incident response at Gemini Health?
answer: Open Settings > Custom Fields, add the field type, and assign it to the incident response forms within the Gemini Health workspace.

question: How do I download historical usage adoption for Helix Labs?
answer: In Analytics > Reports choose usage adoption, set the date window, and export. The file includes every metric for Helix Labs.

question: How do I pause billing for Indigo Travel during billing dispute?
answer: From Billing > Plans click Pause, pick billing dispute as the reason, and the system will freeze charges for Indigo Travel until reactivated.

question: How do I sync Google Workspace contacts for Jupiter Media?
answer: Enable contact sync inside the Google Workspace settings, map the owner field to Jupiter Media, and run a manual sync to verify records.

question: How do I monitor uptime alerts for Krypton Telecom?
answer: Subscribe Krypton Telecom admins to status.example.com and enable webhook alerts under Monitoring > Alerts.

question: What API endpoint retrieves knowledge insights metrics for Lumen Energy?
answer: Use GET /v1/metrics/knowledge insights with the Lumen Energy workspace ID and include the API key in headers.
